args: Heya, Albert. Any new leads on Yurius?
That's a shame. Still, there's no rush.\nTake all the time you need.
(They're all so kindâ€”and I doubt they'd\nhave any problem with my continuing to\ntake advantage of that kindness.)
(Yet I cannot indulge myself like that.\nI cannot cause them any more trouble\nthan I already have.)
(I think it's time. ...Thank you, everyone.\nI will never forget what you did for me.)
I've been looking for him all morning\nand I can't find him.
I'm guessing he's just practicing his\nswordsmanship somewhere like always.
...Hmm? Is that a letter on the table?
Well, don't just stand there and make me\nwonder about what the heck is inside!\nOpen the dang thing already!
I have a bad feeling about this...
(Settling things with Yurius is my issue,\nand mine alone.)
Any fiend who stands in my way\nwill face my lightning!
Hey! Did Albert really fly the coop?!
Gya! And after we spent all that time\ntellin' him not to go it alone!
Grumble about that later, big fella.\nWe need to track him down!
Let's hurryâ€”he can't have gone far!
Fiends. We got scorch marks\nall over the place, too.
Like those made by lightning.\nIs Albert fighting fiends as we speak?
If so, he's been busy. This is a hell of\na lot of scorch marks.
Seems crazy to take on that many\nfiends all by yer lonesome.
...Did you hear that? It sounds like a fiend!
It came from over there! Let's go!
Where are you, Albert?! Say something!
Naturally. But what are you doing here?!
What do you think we're doing?\nWe came after you!
Talking can waitâ€”we need to\ntake care of these fiends first!
Simple?! There were so many of 'em,\nI damn near dulled my axe!
Ya really are on a different level,\nMr. Thunderswift Lord.
You just ran off and left the castle\nwithout saying a word to anyone!\nWe were really worried about you!
We are all with Notte on this one.\nWalking off and leaving your friends\nlike that is cold-hearted indeed.
But I thought I had caused you\nmore than enough trouble already.
It ain't trouble if yer a friend!
Ya shoulda just stayed with us until\nthis whole thing was over.
I was just thinking that friends\nare good things to have.
They sure are! So there's no need to \nbottle everything up any moreâ€”\njust rely on us when you need to.
Very well. But in return, I will help you\nas YOUR friend.
Well, let's get back to the castle!
I've asked Cleo to make loads of food\nto welcome you back.
(One day, I hope you can come\nto our castle, Yurius.)
(If you do, I feel you can change as I didâ€”\nand choose a different path.)
